Quality control report for PACE EWAS analysis of persistent atopic dermatitis

Thomas Battram

Summary of analysis

This study is examining the association between DNA methylation and childhood eczema (up to 10 years). There are 3 definitions of eczema used throughout this study. This report is specific to EWAS of persistent AD (AD by age 2 and persisting to ~ 8-10yrs, controls: no AD by age 10).

For the QC, the checks laid out by the developers of QCEWAS were followed (although the package itself was not used). To examine inflation of results the ewaff package was used to generate lambdas and QQ-plots and the BACON package to estimate inflation and bias factors.

Model a

Logistic regression model:

\[\begin{equation} AD = meth + sex\ (+ selection)\ (+ ancestry)\ (+ batch) \tag{1} \end{equation}\]

where covariates in brackets are applied where appropriate.
